block content

  +state('Arkansas', '/assets/images/flag-arkansas.svg', 'The Natural State', 'June 15, 1836')

  .intro
    p In 1912, the Pine Bluff chapter of the Daughters of the American Revolution held a flag design contest to create a flag for the USS #[em Arkansas].
    p Willie K. Hocker, a local teacher, submitted the winning design which featured three blue stars at the center of a white diamond trimmed in blue and 25 white stars. At the flag committee’s request, the word “Arkanas” was added and the flag was adopted in 1913.
    p The flag has had two small revisions, with its current iteration adopted in 1924.
    p Although unchanged since, it wasn’t signed into law until 1987.

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Flag design
      p The Arkansas flag features a field of red. At the center is a large white diamond, bordered by a band of blue upon which 25 white stars are placed.
      p Within the white diamond the word “Arkanas” is inscribed. Three blue stars are placed below and one blue star placed above.
    .visual.flag
      img(src='/assets/images/flag-arkansas.svg')

  .guide.wide
    .content
      h2 Iconography
      ul.visual.icon-list
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-arkansas-icon-diamond.svg')
          h4 Diamond
          p The diamond shape represents Arkansas as the only diamond-bearing state in the U.S.
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-arkansas-icon-stars.svg')
          h4 25 stars
          p The 25 white stars represent Arkansas as the 25th state to join the Union.
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-arkansas-icon-3-stars.svg')
          h4 3 stars
          p The three stars symbolize two different trios: the three countries to which Arkansas has belonged (Spain, France, and the U.S.) and the first three states formed from the Louisiana Purchase (Louisiana, Missouri and Arkansas).
        li.icon-item
          span.icon: img(src='/assets/images/flag-arkansas-icon-1-star.svg')
          h4 1 star
          p The single star commemorates Arkansas’ secession and role in the Confederate States of America.

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Colors
      p Colors include red, white, and blue. The blue and red match those on the United States flag.
    .visual.colors.primary
      .color
        .sample(class='us-blue')
        .name Blue
        .hex #00205b
        small PMS 281
      .color
        .sample(class='us-red')
        .name Red
        .hex #bg0a30
        small PMS 193
      .color
        .sample(class='white')
        .name White
        .hex #ffffff

  .guide
    .content
      h2 Production
      p The flag should have a proportion of 2:3.
      p If resized, it must maintain these proportions.
    .visual
      img(src='/assets/images/flag-arkansas-dimensions.svg')

  .guide.wide.timeline
    .content
      h2 Previous iterations
      ul.visual.flag-list
        li.flag-item
